        <body>
            <head type="title">On the Road</head>
            <div1 type="part" n="1">
                <div2 type="chapter" n="1">
                    <head>1</head>
                    <p>I first met <persName ref="NC"
                            ><forename>Dean</forename></persName> not long after my wife and I split
                        up. I had just gotten over a serious illness that I won’t bother to talk
                        about, except that it had something to do with the miserably weary split-up
                        and my feeling that everything was dead. With the coming of <persName
                            ref="NC"><forename>Dean</forename>
                            <surname>Moriarty</surname></persName> began the part of my life you
                        could call my life on the road. Before that I’d often dreamed of going West
                        to see the country, always vaguely planning and never taking off. <persName
                            ref="NC"><forename>Dean</forename></persName> is the
                        perfect guy for the road because he actually was born on the road, when his
                        parents were passing through <placeName ref="#SLC">Salt Lake
                            City</placeName> in <date when="1926">1926</date>, in a jalopy, on their way to
                            <placeName ref="LA">Los Angeles</placeName>. First reports of him
                        came to me through <persName ref="HC"
                                ><forename>Chad</forename><surname>King</surname></persName>, who’d
                        shown me a few letters from him written in a <placeName ref="#NM">New
                            Mexico</placeName> whoorm school. I was tremendously interested in the
                        letters because they so naively and sweetly asked <persName ref="HC"><forename>Chad</forename></persName> to teach him all about
                        <persName><forename>Nietzsche</forename></persName> and all the wonderful intellectual things
                        that <persName ref="HC"><forename>Chad</forename></persName>
                        knew. At one point <persName ref="AG"
                                ><forename>Carlo</forename></persName> and I talked about the
                        letters and wondered if we would ever meet the strange <persName ref="NC"
                            
                            ><forename>Dean</forename><surname>Moriarty</surname></persName>. This
                        is all far back, when <persName ref="NC"
                                ><forename>Dean</forename></persName> was not the way he is today,
                        when he was a young jailkid shrouded in mystery. Then news came that
                            <persName ref="NC" type="alias"><forename>Dean</forename></persName>
                        was out of whoorm school and was coming to <placeName ref="NY">New
                            York</placeName> for the first time; also there was talk that he had
                        just married a girl called <persName ref="LAH"
                                ><forename>Marylou</forename></persName>.</p>
                </div2>
